headline: C.H. Robinson Worldwide (NASDAQ:CHRW) Misses Q1 Revenue Estimates
summary: Freight transportation intermediary C.H. Robinson (NASDAQ:CHRW) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales falling 8.3% year on year to $4.05 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.17 per share was 11.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
